Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora from neck join to sharp turn. Clay near fine light red-brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 96, 6 Name Archembrotos.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1095)
